═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
CURSOR RULES — UTILITYNET DEMO — READ BEFORE EVERY ACTION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

ANTI-HALLUCINATION RULES (non-negotiable):

1. PROVE FILES EXIST BEFORE TOUCHING THEM
   Run: ls [filepath] — show output. If ls fails, file doesn't exist.

2. NEVER CLAIM A COMMAND PASSED WITHOUT SHOWING OUTPUT
   Wrong: "all checks passed"
   Right: [paste actual terminal output]

3. ONE FEATURE AT A TIME
   Build → commit → push → report hash → wait for Claude to verify.
   Never batch multiple features in one response.

4. LOCKED = UNTOUCHABLE
   Never modify a LOCKED feature. New requirements = new feature ID.

5. NEVER STUB A CHECK SCRIPT
   return { pass: true } is forbidden. Real checks only.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ENVIRONMENT RULES (learned the hard way):

- Only ONE Vite dev server at a time.
  Before running anything, check: lsof -i :5173 -i :5174 -i :5175
  Kill all but one. Multiple servers = false test results.

- Always use explicit URL for demo scripts:
  DEMO_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5173 npm run demo:[script]

- Terminal always starts at: ethan@Ethans-MacBook-Air-Tank utilitynet-demo
  All demo commands need: cd demo first.

- Three terminals for dev:
  Terminal 1: cd demo && npm run mock
  Terminal 2: cd demo && npm run dev
  Terminal 3: cd demo && [demo/heal commands]

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
TECHNICAL RULES:

- AppStore = React Context + useReducer. NO Zustand. Ever.
- Do not touch auto-heal.mjs.
- Do not use "Watchdog" branding in any UI — use "System Health".
- All Playwright demo scripts use page.evaluate() for DOM clicks,
  not clickWithCursor, for elements that may be out of viewport.
- Always scroll to top after Emberlyn interactions before clicking
  page header buttons.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
DEBUGGING RULES:

- Max 3 guesses on any bug. After 3 fails → inject diagnostic
  console.log code and run it to get real data first.
- If diagnostic mode doesn't resolve → escalate to Codex.
- Codex is the tiebreaker for doom loops.
- NEVER use Chrome browser tools — wrong machine.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
COMMIT FORMAT (end every task with this exactly):

  git add -A && git commit -m "[description]" && git push && echo "COMMIT HASH:" && git rev-parse HEAD

Report the hash back so Claude can verify the actual repo state.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SESSION START — DO THIS FIRST, EVERY TIME:

Run these commands and show full output:

  git log --oneline -3
  cat demo/FEATURE_REGISTRY.json | grep -E '"status"' | head -25
  ls demo/src/components/CoachRail* 2>/dev/null || echo "CoachRail: NOT BUILT"
  ls demo/public/audio 2>/dev/null || echo "Audio: NOT GENERATED"

This tells Claude the current build state.
Do not start building until you've shown this output.

